### **Summary Table**

| Step           | Action                                    | Command/Note                 |
|----------------|-------------------------------------------|------------------------------|
| 1. Place routers| Packet Tracer workspace                   |                              |
| 2. Connect routers| Use cables, assign interfaces            | Choose unique subnets        |
| 3. Assign IPs  | Router config > Interface > IP address     | Set for each interface       |
| 4. Configure RIP| CLI: `router rip` etc.                    | Repeat for all routers       |
| 5. Configure OSPF| CLI: `router ospf` etc.                   | Use correct wildcard masks   |
| 6. Test        | Ping between routers/PCs                   | `ping <ip>`                  |
| 7. Analyze     | `show ip route` on routers                 | Check learned routes         |
| 8. Report      | Document config, output, success           | Screenshots, explanations    |

